  <abstract>Jeff Montgomery, USMC, wrote this letter to his future wife Ruth Hopper in Jackson, Tennessee. Montgomery is in training at the Marine Corps Barracks on Parris Island. He enlisted only a few weeks before the armistice. His letter discussed drilling and training. He mentioned the receipt of their new Marine uniforms in "winter green." He explained that they were receiving their typhoid shots the following day.</abstract>
